def: The act of disavowing, disclaiming, or disowning; rejection anddenial.An earnest disavowal of fear often proceeds from fear. Richardson.
To insert in a catalogue; to register; to catalogue. [R.]Coles.
Of or pertaining to the Angles.-- n.
The state or quality of being knowable. Locke.
A solid having many summits or angular points; a polyhedron.
To separate, as things mixed. Bacon.
Containing or producing pap; like pap. [R.] Arbuthnot.
imp. & p. p. of Refind, v. t.
To starve with hunger; to famish. [Obs.] Shak.
